
# AnimatePage PRD Document

## 1. Product Overview
AnimatePage is a visually stunning web page featuring high-quality animations that create an engaging user experience. The page will showcase various animation techniques including CSS transitions, SVG animations, and JavaScript-powered motion effects.

## 2. Target Users
- Web designers looking for animation inspiration
- Developers wanting to implement modern animation techniques
- Marketing teams needing eye-catching landing pages
- UI/UX designers creating interactive prototypes

## 3. Core Features

### 3.1 Hero Section Animation
- Smooth parallax scrolling effect
- Animated gradient background
- Typing animation for headline text
- Floating elements with subtle motion

### 3.2 Interactive Elements
- Button hover effects with ripple animations
- Animated form fields with floating labels
- Progress loading animations
- 3D card flip interactions

### 3.3 Scroll-triggered Animations
- Fade-in effects as user scrolls
- Path drawing animations for SVG elements
- Staggered element reveals
- Perspective shift animations

### 3.4 Micro-interactions
- Animated hamburger menu
- Loading spinners and progress bars
- Notification badge animations
- Tooltip reveal effects

## 4. Technical Specifications

### 4.1 Animation Technologies
- CSS Animations and Transitions
- GSAP (GreenSock Animation Platform)
- WebGL for complex 3D effects (optional)
- Lottie for After Effects animations
- SVG animations using SMIL

### 4.2 Performance Considerations
- Hardware acceleration for smooth animations
- Debounced scroll events
- Animation frame optimization
- Reduced motion preferences support
- Lazy loading for heavy assets

## 5. Design Requirements

### 5.1 Visual Style
- Modern, clean aesthetic
- Vibrant color palette with animated gradients
- Ample white space to highlight animations
- Consistent motion design language

### 5.2 Motion Principles
- All animations should follow easing curves
- Maximum animation duration: 800ms
- Choreographed sequencing for complex animations
- Attention to motion choreography

## 6. Implementation Phases

### Phase 1: Foundation
- Setup animation framework
- Implement core scrolling behavior
- Create basic component animations

### Phase 2: Enhancement
- Add interactive elements
- Implement advanced SVG animations
- Optimize performance

### Phase 3: Polish
- Fine-tune timing and easing
- Add accessibility features
- Implement reduced motion alternative

## 7. Accessibility Requirements
- Provide reduced motion alternatives
- Ensure proper color contrast
- Keyboard navigable interactive elements
- ARIA labels for animated content

## 8. Success Metrics
- 90+ Lighthouse performance score
- Sub-50ms animation frame times
- 95%+ supported browser coverage
- Positive user feedback on animation quality
